<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>AIR CONDITIONING - HEATER SYSTEM: 2000, 4000, AND 8000 - Before 12/06/1994 - REMOVE AND INSTALL - HEATER
        CORE - HEATER ONLY SYSTEM
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>HEATER CORE - HEATER ONLY SYSTEM</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Drain engine cooling system.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen hose clamps at heater core and remove hoses (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601412">Figure 12</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1601412" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1601412" filename="../figg16/G1601412.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="514px" scalefitheight="472px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 12. Heater Core Removal - Heater Only Models</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. SCREW</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. BOTTOM SEAL</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. TOP SEAL</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. HEATER CORE</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. FRONT SEAL</callout1>
                        <callout1>6. BLEND-AIR DOOR</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove cover from the passenger side of the instrument panel.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove screws attaching cover to heater housing and remove cover.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the four screws attaching the heater core pipes to the dash panel and remove the
                    heater core.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect the hoses and seals. If damaged or deteriorated, replace.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the heater core in the heater housing making sure that front, top and bottom
                    seals are in position (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601412">Figure 12</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install four screws attaching the heater core to the heating housing.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install two screws attaching the heater core pipes to the dash panel.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the heater hoses on the heater core pipes and tighten the hose clamps.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Refill the engine cooling system.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Set the temperature control knob to HOT. Operate engine and check for coolant leaks and
                    coolant flow through the heater core.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Replace the covers in the heater unit housing and the right side instrument panel.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
